        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 4:18PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Wildorado, or 12 miles northeast of Vega, moving
northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boys Ranch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
